---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Wave Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for Wave, the macOS dictation app with local transcription and optional cloud AI features."
>
  <section class="relative z-10 px-6 pb-24 pt-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <div class="reveal rounded-[28px] border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-8 shadow-[0_30px_120px_rgba(7,10,24,0.35)] backdrop-blur md:p-12">
        <p class="mb-3 text-[12px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-cyan-300/80">
          Privacy Policy
        </p>
        <h1 class="max-w-3xl text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white md:text-5xl">
          Wave is built to keep voice workflows simple and transparent.
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-[16px] leading-8 text-slate-300">
          This Privacy Policy explains what data Wave may process, when that data stays on your Mac,
          and when it is sent to third-party providers you choose to use.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-[14px] text-slate-400">Last updated: April 4, 2026</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-6">
        <article class="reveal rounded-[24px] border border-white/8 bg-slate-950/50 p-7">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">1. What Wave Does</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[15px] leading-8 text-slate-300">
            Wave is a macOS dictation app that records audio from your microphone, transcribes speech
            into text, and can optionally send text to an AI provider to generate or rewrite content.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="reveal rounded-[24px] border border-white/8 bg-slate-950/50 p-7">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">2. Information Wave May Process</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[15px] leading-8 text-slate-300">
            Depending on how you use the app, Wave may process microphone audio, transcribed text,
            prompts you send to AI mode, selected microphone metadata, custom vocabulary, snippets,
            and local app settings.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="reveal rounded-[24px] border border-white/8 bg-slate-950/50 p-7">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">3. Local Transcription</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[15px] leading-8 text-slate-300">
            When you use on-device transcription, audio processing happens locally on your Mac using
            the models and runtime included with the app. In that mode, your audio is not sent to
            Wave’s servers.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="reveal rounded-[24px] border border-white/8 bg-slate-950/50 p-7">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">4. Cloud Transcription and AI Mode</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[15px] leading-8 text-slate-300">
            If you enable cloud transcription or AI mode, Wave sends the necessary audio or text to
            the third-party provider you configure in order to return a result. This may include
            microphone audio, transcribed text, prompts, and generated responses.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[15px] leading-8 text-slate-300">
            Your use of those features is also subject to the privacy practices and terms of the
            third-party provider you choose.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="reveal rounded-[24px] border border-white/8 bg-slate-950/50 p-7">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">5. API Keys and Credentials</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[15px] leading-8 text-slate-300">
            Wave may store API keys or related configuration locally on your device so the app can
            access the providers you configure. Wave does not sell your API keys and does not use
            them for advertising.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="reveal rounded-[24px] border border-white/8 bg-slate-950/50 p-7">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">6. History, Snippets, and Settings</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[15px] leading-8 text-slate-300">
            Wave may store transcription history, snippets, preferences, and device selections locally
            on your Mac to support core functionality. That data is used to operate the app experience
            and is not shared for advertising.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="reveal rounded-[24px] border border-white/8 bg-slate-950/50 p-7">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">7. Analytics and Website Data</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[15px] leading-8 text-slate-300">
            The Wave marketing website may use privacy-focused website analytics to understand traffic
            and improve the site. This policy applies to both the website and the app where relevant,
            but website analytics are separate from microphone audio and transcription processing in
            the macOS app.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="reveal rounded-[24px] border border-white/8 bg-slate-950/50 p-7">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">8. Data Sharing</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[15px] leading-8 text-slate-300">
            Wave does not sell your personal information. Data is only shared with third-party service
            providers when needed to perform the cloud features you choose to use, such as transcription
            or AI generation.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="reveal rounded-[24px] border border-white/8 bg-slate-950/50 p-7">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">9. Your Choices</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[15px] leading-8 text-slate-300">
            You can choose local transcription instead of cloud processing, remove saved history or
            snippets from within the app, and stop using any configured cloud provider at any time by
            removing its credentials from the app.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="reveal rounded-[24px] border border-white/8 bg-slate-950/50 p-7">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">10. Contact</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[15px] leading-8 text-slate-300">
            If you have privacy questions about Wave, contact:
            <a href="mailto:hello@wave.mxv.sh" class="text-cyan-300 no-underline hover:text-cyan-200">
              hello@mxv.sh
            </a>
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
